#* {{quote-song|author=Michael Flanders|authorlink=Michael Flanders|title=A Transport of Delight|album={{w|At the Drop of a Hat}}|location=[New York, N.Y.?]|publisher={{w|Parlophone}}|date=2 May 1959|note=audio recording of a musical revue|oclc=220646045|id=PCSO 3001|passage='''Omnibus''', my friend Mr. [[w:Donald Swann|[Donald] Swann]] informs me, comes from the Latin ''omnibus'', meaning to or for by with or from everybody, which is a very good description. Well, this song is about a bus, it's wittily subtitled—I thought of this—'A Transport of Delight'.|brackets=on}}
#* {{quote-video|actor={{w|Rowan Atkinson}}|role=[[w:Edmund Blackadder#Ebenezer Blackadder (Victorian London)|Ebenezer Blackadder]]|title={{w|Blackadder's Christmas Carol}}|writer={{w|Richard Curtis}} and {{w|Ben Elton}}|location=London|publisher={{w|BBC}}|date=23 December 1988|oclc=795996742|passage={{w|Baldrick}}, I want you to take this [money] and go out, and buy a turkey so large you'd think its mother had been rogered by an '''omnibus'''.}}
